McAuley Schenker Group
McAuley-Schenker Group was a band featuring core members Robin McAuley (vocals) and Michael Schenker (guitar), a successor to Schenker's earlier Michael Schenker Group. The group released several albums before disbanding. Their debut album Perfect Timing was released in 1987, and yielded their first hit "Gimme Your Love". Two years later, Save Yourself arrived, giving this incarnation of MSG their biggest hit with the power ballad "Anytime". M.S.G. followed in 1991, and Unplugged - Live came out in 1993.
